               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus donation of property from Egypt. A wife donates the third part of a monastery to her husband on condition that he does not throw her out as long as she lives and as long as she does not commit adultery. Includes an oath by God Almighty and the emperor Justinus I or II</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 12.8 x 30.2 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">15 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers on the recto</note>
                     <note type="general">Small lower margin(?); left margin of 2 cm.; small right margin</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 728 was formerly P.Duk.inv. LK76 1</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
